auto recalls usually come about in one of two ways sometimes automakers discover a defect notify the national highway traffic safety administration and voluntarily issue a recall in other cases the safety agency learns about defects when consumers contact its auto safety hot line the agency investigates the complaints and those investigations sometimes result in safety recalls consumers who think their vehicles have safety defects can make reports to the agency by calling the hot line at 888 327 4236 the hearing impaired can call 800 424 9153 reports may be filed online at wwwnhtsadotgov by selecting complaint form from the bottom of the left hand index cheryl jensen

